      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving mill utilizes six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is routed through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a torque-sensing limited-slip differential. The chassis remains taut with a reinforced rear subframe\u2014a critical preventive measure for this platform\u2014and refreshed polyurethane bushings. Recent maintenance includes a comprehensive valve clearance adjustment and a cooling system overhaul. While the car shows minor aesthetic patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the mechanical synchronization and 50/50 weight distribution remain quintessential M-division. A purist-spec example ready for the backroads.",
